verse_part: You will make known to me
And from those who hated me,
those who rose up against me
those who rise up against me;
I will give thanks to You
we will set up our banners
of those who wait for You
that I would not go down
I will give thanks to You
and from those who persecute me
with those who contend with me;
from him who is too strong
And why have you become disturbed
those who rise up against us
as of a woman in childbirth
and state the case in order
But as for me, I am like a green
For the choir director; according to Mahalath. A Maskil of David. The fool
of him who encamped against you;
they bear a grudge against me
against those who were at peace with him;
I will give thanks to You,
I will sing praises to You
He will sweep them away with a whirlwind
away from those who rise up against me
So they will make him stumble
The women who proclaim the good tidings
of those whom You have wounded
But as for me, I will hope
those who are far from You
of those who rise against You
It is I who have firmly
were cast into a dead sleep
to Him who is to be feared
and caused them to pass through

You have been full of wrath
You have swept them away like a flood
according to the fear that is due You
That we may sing for joy
I will set him securely on high
like that of the wild ox
is His, for it was He who made
So that they will not return

and in the shadow of death

I shall give thanks to You,
and I give thanks to You;
of those who are at ease

But as for those who turn aside
to the roof of my mouth
I will sing praises to You
I will give thanks to You,
those who rise up against You
So that I may give thanks
Your will, For You are my God
that You take knowledge of him?
